  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka Treasuries yields up over 400bp",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s Treasuries yields rose over 400 basis points across maturities ahead of a monetary policy meeting, data from the state debt office showed.",
        "The three month yield went up 423 basis points to 28.08 percent from 23.85 percent a week earlier",
        "The six month yield went up 434 basis points to 28.74\tfrom 24.4 percent.",
        "The 12 month yield went up 427 percent to 28.11 from 23.84 percent.",
        "The debt office offered 70 billion rupees of bills and sold all.",
        "Sri Lanka\u2019s inflation hit 56.4 percent in June 2022 after two years of money printing and a botched float with a surrender requirement. (Colombo/July06/2022)"
      ],
